Dialogue: 10,0:01:15.47,0:01:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! It's the Northern Corridor!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:26.14,0:01:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The legends of my northern tribe \Nhave proved correct!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:30.15,0:01:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's time for the people to set out in search of a new world. To cross the corridor!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.26,0:01:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,O God, you guided us along the way.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:58.20,0:02:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You helped us survive\N starvation and freezing.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.01,0:02:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We will head to the warm and fertile land, the promised paradise. {rakuen / paradise is the title of the original book this is based upon}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.07,0:03:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no ordinary cave.\NIt's more like a rift in the Earth.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.20,0:03:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The lake I wanted to show you is hidden\N all the way inside this deep cave.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.87,0:03:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A mysterious underground lake \Nyou've just discovered?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.16,0:03:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Pulling the cord from a generator to such depths was no small feat, was it?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.50,0:03:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it long enough?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.63,0:03:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it covers about half the path.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.09,0:03:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, we'll have to rely \Non these headlamps.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.14,0:03:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.93,0:03:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I already climbed down there once \Nto see if it's safe.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.22,0:03:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! I'll get things ready.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.40,0:03:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I still can't believe it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.53,0:03:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, in the middle of this desert, a conical crater resembling a doodlebug pit trap,{/mortar-shaped crater; https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antlion}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.03,0:03:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lake deep inside it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.92,0:04:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, this is actually amazing.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.34,0:04:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of years ago, \Nthis place was at the bottom of the ocean.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.80,0:04:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.80,0:04:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll know after you've explored it. {this "sa" at the end is probably by the bogud (the younger guy) but I'm not sure and its kinda unimportant, would mean something like "really?" here}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.93,0:04:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Radiolaria, foraminifera, and fusulinida...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.27,0:04:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The organisms that lived in different eras have accumulated here
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.23,0:04:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and formed layered sediments.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.27,0:04:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we won't just be going down to the depths of the Earth,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.86,0:04:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll be traveling to the distant past through the ages of time.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.86,0:04:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.12,0:04:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, as the weight of time fills you, \Nyou'll find yourself by an underground lake.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.24,0:04:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The air and the peculiar stalactite patterns \Nof that place will move you deeply. {, I hope}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.79,0:04:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, I hope this tour will inspire the luminary of current composers,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.34,0:04:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Leslie Mardoff, to write a new concerto or symphony.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.80,0:04:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why the famous music producer \NGilbert brought me all the way here?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.77,0:04:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I hope for that too.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.31,0:04:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good. Because if this plan succeeds...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.44,0:04:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm confident it {\i1}will{\i0} succeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.56,0:05:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll take the world by storm.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.48,0:05:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.37,0:05:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.66,0:05:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.79,0:05:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Leslie.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.54,0:05:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd agreed to keep this project\N secret until we were done.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.30,0:05:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still good, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.55,0:05:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.80,0:05:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you didn't tell a third party\N that we were coming here, did you?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.72,0:05:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Well, about that...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.99,0:05:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better be careful.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.87,0:05:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Leslie Mardoff is a famous playboy.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.50,0:06:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the suicide attempt by an idol he was dating at the time?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:06.30,0:06:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it was before we hired you,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.76,0:06:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was all over the media at the time, \Nso you have to know.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.31,0:06:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's actually gotten into other,\N similar scandals too.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.68,0:06:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,With an actress, a singer, a model, \Nand even one of his innocent fans. {/layman}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.06,0:06:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got quite a reputation.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.73,0:06:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But no other composer rivals Leslie Mardoff\N in popularity among the young.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.53,0:06:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.74,0:06:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's undeniable.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.62,0:06:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Every piece he writes gets\N a rapturous reception from critics.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.91,0:06:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,His newly released CDs \Nalways top the US charts.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.25,0:06:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a fan of his too.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.75,0:06:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean, of the music he writes.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.38,0:06:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, it's going to be\N the first time we meet in person.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.63,0:06:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, maybe I shouldn't have \Ntaken on this project?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.47,0:06:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.18,0:06:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The brilliant young composer Leslie Mardoff\N shapes the music of our era.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.52,0:07:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You were given a chance to land\N the first successful interview with him.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.19,0:07:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like that would definitely make the headlines for next month's issue.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.27,0:07:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But be careful, Flora.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.82,0:07:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Leslie Mardoff despises the media\N with a passion and has a difficult personality.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.66,0:07:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Companies fight tooth and nail for a chance to interview him,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.78,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but he just turns them all down.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.24,0:07:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I'm saying all that is...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.12,0:07:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You've worked here for less than two years.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.15,0:07:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still a rookie by journalistic standards,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.54,0:07:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,yet you landed an interview\N with him effortlessly.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.96,0:07:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All it took was one phone call, didn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.51,0:07:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I find that hard to take at face value.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.30,0:07:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe it either.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.30,0:07:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting near the phone \Nfor a while, doubting myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.26,0:07:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Whatever. Even if he turns me down, so be it." I made up my mind,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.64,0:07:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,mustered up my courage, and dialed.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.27,0:07:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I got lucky. He was there and said "Okay" without a second thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.86,0:07:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But he said that to get in the mood \Nfor the next symphony he's composing,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.40,0:07:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to an underground lake,\Nand he'll let me take pictures of it as a bonus.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.28,0:07:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how surprised I was!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.91,0:07:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if that's some new ploy \Nfor picking up girls.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.91,0:08:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.62,0:08:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How could he know what kind of girl I am \Njust from hearing my voice on the phone?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.42,0:08:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was kidding.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.38,0:08:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But this certainly has a mysterious feel to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.13,0:08:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Flora, I'm sure your strong resolve \N provided you a stroke of good luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.26,0:08:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best, and I'm sure \Nyou'll turn this into a great scoop.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.10,0:08:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My, oh my! Even the bugs are attracted to your extraordinary luck! {a JP superstition, see https://uranai.callat.jp/posts/1125}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.07,0:08:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Better not scratch it too much, \Nor it will swell.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.15,0:08:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, not again!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.11,0:08:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This just happens to me from time to time.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.61,0:08:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These red spots appear out of nowhere, \Neven without any bugs biting me.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.33,0:08:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But it'll be gone soon enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.62,0:08:49.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,So it's another one of our playboy's tricks? \NHm. As if I'd ever fall for that!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.13,0:08:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You invited some female journalist here?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.92,0:09:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Leslie, why are you like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.22,0:09:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get so mad, Gilbert.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.31,0:09:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Our interview isn't scheduled for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.31,0:09:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do it tomorrow afternoon \Nin the motel lobby, after we're done here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.57,0:09:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably also promised her \Nto come back here
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.86,0:09:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and take some pictures with \Nthe underground lake as the backdrop.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.20,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of course you'd be kind enough \Nto assume some contemplative pose for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.41,0:09:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a free time interview, \Nso it shouldn't interfere with my work.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.41,0:09:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid, that habit is gonna be your ruin.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.41,0:09:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.71,0:09:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean {\i1}that{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.00,0:09:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever a pretty girl is involved, \Nyou start fawning all over her.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.55,0:09:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you have agreed \Nif it'd been a seasoned veteran reporter? {lit: with moss on his face - means "old/old-fashioned"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.64,0:09:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I knew about your playboy demeanor, \Nbut I didn't think it was {\i1}this{\i0} bad.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:43.64,0:09:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After just hearing her voice on the phone!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.73,0:09:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Gilbert!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.81,0:09:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I had any ulterior motives in mind
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.15,0:09:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,when I accepted an interview with her.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.11,0:09:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For starters, that'd be \Na comically elaborate scheme. {lit: first, if that was true, isn't it comedic?}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.28,0:10:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I still have no idea \Nwhat kind of person that reporter is.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.70,0:10:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when I received \Na call from her that night...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.12,0:10:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Leslie Mardoff?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.00,0:10:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Flora. I work as an editor at {\i1}Log Book{\i0} Inc.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.67,0:10:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Flora?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.55,0:10:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, is something wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.97,0:10:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it sounds completely bonkers,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.22,0:10:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but when I first heard her voice, \NI was overwhelmed by dizziness.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.81,0:10:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why, but I felt like the passion \Nof a distant past had been awakened.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.86,0:10:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As though a stream of cold water had suddenly run through dry, parched land.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.65,0:10:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A shock went all through my body, \Nelectrifying every cell in it. {lit: every cell swelled and exploded}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.00,0:10:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard of love at first sight.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.91,0:10:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but I've never heard of anyone getting \Nso agitated by the mere sound of a voice.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.46,0:10:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine she must have\N a very captivating voice.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.26,0:10:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This magazine reporter named Flora.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.53,0:11:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.78,0:11:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had proper illumination here, {/pulled the cord to}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.45,0:11:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the sight unfolding before your eyes\N would be much more subtle and profound.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.00,0:11:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, the weight of time pressing down on me here
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.54,0:11:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,feels oddly familiar to my body.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.97,0:11:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Leslie.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.34,0:11:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've wanted to ask you for a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.64,0:11:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up with that stone pendant you keep toying with?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.02,0:11:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean this?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.52,0:11:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite old.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.65,0:11:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds me of ancient people's amulets \Nfrom museum exhibitions.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.11,0:12:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? It has a drawing on it too.\NA red deer, huh? Interesting.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.66,0:12:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert, I told you before
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.82,0:12:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that the blood in my veins is about a quarter Native American, didn't I?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.99,0:12:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Natives' oral tradition holds that \Ndeer are endowed with a strong spirit.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.33,0:12:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is my charm.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.46,0:12:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.42,0:12:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For a long time, I've been pursuing one particular theme.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.88,0:12:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it'd be more correct to say\N I've been pursuing a certain image.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.43,0:12:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to know where my ancestors,\N the Native Americans, originally came from.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.10,0:12:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A long time ago... \NRight, over 10,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.10,0:12:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the closing years of the Pleistocene epoch, {actually "diluvial epoch of ice age" but the term seems to be a little obsolete; actually you could just write "in the closing years of ice age" or 11000 years ago bc it's effectively the same thing but without overloading the text with scientific garbage; here's how the book puts it: "It was said that more than\Nten thousand years ago, during the final epoch of the Diluvial Ice\NAge, the ancestors of the Native Americans crossed over the\NBering Strait from Asia into a new land in several migratory\Nwaves. This glacial road of the far north was called "Beringia."}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.61,0:12:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,my ancestors came here \Nfrom a distant region in Asia.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.44,0:12:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They crossed the Bering Strait \Nand populated this continent.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.28,0:12:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Those Native Americans used\N a glacial road in the far north.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.49,0:12:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called "Beringia." {actually he says "indians called it beringia" but that's obviously a scriptwriters mistake because the indians of 10000 years ago had no idea who vitus bering was and they left no written sources anyhow: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beringia}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.87,0:12:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Beringia.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.62,0:12:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind that word lies the life, death, \Nand essence of my race. {/all things being in flux through the endless circle of birth, death, and rebirth; the circle of transmigration}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.63,0:13:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that this place once\N used to be the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.13,0:13:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It might well be that we're currently standing on the stratum
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.80,0:13:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that corresponds to the time of Beringia,\Nwhen my native ancestors decided to cross.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.18,0:13:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear them.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.85,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The agitated voices of their ice-bound journey, echoing through time.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.06,0:13:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The squeaking of carts, \Nthe neighing of horses.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.94,0:13:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single sound becomes a particle \Nthat enters my body.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.97,0:13:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There, eat this!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.51,0:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.98,0:14:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.23,0:14:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for Bogud, \NI saw him going to the valley, alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.03,0:14:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? What'll I do with that kid?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.52,0:14:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.10,0:14:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Fayau.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.35,0:14:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom has been looking for you for a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:40.60,0:14:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She has?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.23,0:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, for a few days now! {in the book, Bogud left for several days with food to finish the portrait, so here it may be that she means "mom's been looking for you for several days"}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.32,0:14:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She was sure you were slacking\N off somewhere, as usual.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:47.24,0:14:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll probably give you a scolding!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.72,0:15:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.00,0:15:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.63,0:15:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it right there, you lazy young man!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.46,0:15:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it, I said!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.63,0:15:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Bogud.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.30,0:15:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure you're turning thirteen this spring.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:10.63,0:15:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.14,0:15:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,According to our laws, a boy who turns thirteen must go out hunting alone. {/this village}{in book: When boys came of age at thirteen, they went out hunting\Nalone, bringing back the spirit of their first kill as their own. A\Nman was to protect that spirit for his entire life. If the spirit's\N9\NPARADISE\Npower was feeble, the man was destined to die prematurely. If\Nstrong, he would be saved by this endowment alone in any life or\Ndeath situation. With that first kill, his fate was written. The age\Nof thirteen was therefore a milestone in every man's life.}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.68,0:15:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope this fact hasn't completely slipped your mind, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.69,0:15:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.11,0:15:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When summer comes, I'll start training.\NAnd when fall comes, I'll go hunting.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.31,0:15:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so inept, the most impressive prey you'd be able to hunt down is a pig.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.61,0:15:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But good luck all the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.28,0:15:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the first animal you bring down
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.58,0:15:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will become your guardian spirit, deciding your whole life.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.25,0:15:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If you bring back a pig's spirit, you'll never have trouble finding something to chew.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.83,0:15:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But eventually you might end up \Nbecoming a chronic glutton. {yume: 0:15:38.10 Extra TLC needed for this one. I hear "buta no seirei wo ereba, sore wa maa, kuu ni wa komaranai darou ga, aru toki -- kuu to iku koto ni naru kamoshirenai" Can't pick out the muffled word for the life of me.}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.21,0:15:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, animals like pigs are only born \Nto be eaten later by humans.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.97,0:15:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What a spiteful elder.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.64,0:16:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Bah!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.11,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, bringing a pig would be a disaster!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Even you of all people should be able to hunt down a rabbit.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.57,0:16:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The rabbit's spirit isn't bad. \NIt's nimble and cautious.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.87,0:16:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Though he might seem placid, \Nhe's actually quite courageous.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.37,0:16:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I have a rabbit\N as my guardian spirit myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.38,0:16:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course. So that's why you drink \Nuntil your eyes turn red.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.34,0:16:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.13,0:16:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to kill \Neither a pig or a rabbit.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.30,0:16:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal I'm gonna hunt down is...\Na red deer!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.14,0:16:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A red deer?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.52,0:16:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good one. Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.85,0:16:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Go and tell that to our elder.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.44,0:16:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll burst out laughing in your face.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.49,0:16:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, back when I was around your age,\NI dreamed of that too, once or twice.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.92,0:16:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.71,0:17:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The legendary red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.83,0:17:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They say the red deer has the strongest spirit of all the animals out there.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.26,0:17:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Since time immemorial, every boy\N approaching his thirteenth summer
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.05,0:17:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,has wanted to fell a red deer. \NThat's right, every single one.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.77,0:17:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But even to this day, \Nno one's succeeded.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.40,0:17:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember Koriko?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.52,0:17:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He also went on a journey \Nto catch a red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.53,0:17:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a hefty fella.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.45,0:17:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,People gossiped he was gonna be \Nour tribe's future leader.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.32,0:17:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a promising fella too. {big-hearted}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.54,0:17:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a tale it was. In the fall,\N he went to the mountains alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.25,0:17:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't return all through the winter.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.67,0:17:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He only showed up in the spring, \Nwhen the ice at Selenge River thawed.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.22,0:18:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Gaunt and emaciated.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.22,0:18:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Lifeless like a ghost.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.14,0:18:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, nobody even realized \Nit was him, Koriko.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.02,0:18:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He was bedridden for the next four years \Nuntil his untimely death.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.32,0:18:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was only 17.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.12,0:18:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What animal did Koriko fell?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.28,0:18:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but you can be sure \Nit wasn't a red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.00,0:18:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a bad thing to allow yourself to dream big,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.25,0:18:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't you get carried away. {...by it and forget your limits}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.21,0:18:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see a rabbit... You get a rabbit!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.55,0:18:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It tastes good enough too.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.30,0:18:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing wrong with\N a rabbit's spirit, Bogud.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.01,0:18:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd really appreciate it if you helped\N me with housework a bit more.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.77,0:18:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even your little sisters are doing what they can.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.19,0:18:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are you doing\N with all your free time?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.32,0:18:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing, really.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.23,0:18:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably hiding somewhere \Nand drawing whatever pictures he wants.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.70,0:19:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're serious about going hunting, \Nyou need to start practicing with a bow!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.24,0:19:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you draw last time?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.87,0:19:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I drew...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.87,0:19:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the usual things: flowers, cows...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.75,0:19:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't been drawing\N humans, have you?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.80,0:19:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I haven't.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.05,0:19:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good. Nothing wrong\N with drawing pictures.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.47,0:19:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can draw cows and horses all you want \Nand do well in our Tangad tribe. {translation from book tho we kinda hear Tangad so idk, feel free to replace}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.02,0:19:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But not humans.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.56,0:19:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Doncha ever dare draw humans.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.11,0:19:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's another one of our tribe's laws. \NYou know, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.32,0:19:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.87,0:19:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But Dad, why {\i1}is{\i0} that? \NWhy can't I draw humans?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.37,0:19:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.21,0:19:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't it obvious?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.34,0:20:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, do you know?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.68,0:20:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's a mystery to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.18,0:20:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You should try asking the elder.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.55,0:20:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to know?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.68,0:20:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.15,0:20:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, truth be told, \Nyou're good at drawing.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.98,0:20:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you can become my assistant \Nand draw pictures that we'll dedicate to God.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.78,0:20:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,For such an outcome, \Nit'd be better if I told you now, perhaps.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.29,0:20:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.49,0:20:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.58,0:20:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how should I put it?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.77,0:20:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we don't have to worry \Nabout others overhearing us.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.40,0:21:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. This is very important, \Nso don't you ever tell anyone else.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.40,0:21:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.45,0:21:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you draw a picture of a person, \Nyou'll lose that person forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.33,0:21:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Death or lifelong separation... \NIt could be either.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.96,0:21:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In a sense, it's a curse. \NIf this secret became widely known,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.92,0:21:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,well, people would spend all day smearing the Earth with the faces of their enemies. {Lit: the ground would soon be covered in people's faces}{from the book: If this became widely known, the land\Nwould soon be overrun with those exiled in hatred. Because\Neveryone has enemies. It would destroy our clan.}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.59,0:21:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's how jealous humans are.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.81,0:21:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how resentful they are,\N deep in their hearts.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.85,0:21:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason, \Nit's customary not to say {\i1}why{\i0},
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.94,0:21:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,just that drawing people is a no-no\N and don't ask questions.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.37,0:21:51.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's too unreasonable to be true.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.66,0:21:54.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,I carved it because I love Fayau.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.29,0:21:57.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,And the price is death\N or lifelong separation?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:03.00,0:22:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.88,0:22:08.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's it. The spirit of the red deer \Nwill simply shrug off the curse.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.76,0:22:10.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's the strongest of all.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:11.14,0:22:14.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,This autumn, I'll hunt down \Nthe legendary red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.06,0:22:19.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,And then... And then, I'll take Fayau \Nas my wife, and I'll make her happy!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.42,0:22:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud, don't lose any food along the way.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:41.88,0:22:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And be sure to come back before winter!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:44.42,0:22:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, a bird in the hand is worth\N two in the bush. A rabbit is fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:48.38,0:22:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you catch a rabbit, eat it \Nand come back before it starts to snow!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:52.93,0:22:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh? Our Bogud is finally setting out?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:56.43,0:22:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you don't forget \Nto aim for the pig's butt.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:59.19,0:23:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's big enough so you\N probably won't miss.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:07.94,0:23:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:09.91,0:23:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud, stay strong!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:12.03,0:23:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember to be careful!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:12.38,0:24:16.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,No. My target is the legendary red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.53,0:24:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to be a horse. \NYou can live on nothing but grass.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:48.38,0:24:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up! C'mon!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:53.84,0:24:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to keep going. \NIs this really how you want to die?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:58.39,0:24:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up now!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:27.67,0:25:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to stay focused. \NIf I doze off now, I'll freeze to death.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:36.05,0:25:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so hungry.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:38.72,0:25:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't eaten in three days.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:48.86,0:25:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A mouse?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:50.36,0:25:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I could eat a mouse!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:57.32,0:26:01.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm so hungry and exhausted, \NI can't even catch a single mouse.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:03.50,0:26:05.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:05.21,0:26:07.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,What's the good of catching a mouse?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:07.25,0:26:10.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll just get a filthy spirit \Nthat begets diseases. {I... highly doubt they knew that much about rodents back in stone age}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:13.38,0:26:15.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's how it was for Koriko.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:15.42,0:26:19.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,Koriko succumbed to his hunger \Nand ate a mouse.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:20.55,0:26:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The red deer, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:23.26,0:26:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if there really is one.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:27.02,0:26:31.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,I should've followed Dad's advice \Nand settled for a rabbit.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:31.31,0:26:35.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,When it was still autumn, \NI could've caught all the rabbits I wanted.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:47.08,0:26:49.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,I mustn't fall asleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:49.96,0:26:51.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Mustn't sleep...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.75,0:26:53.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,Mustn't...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.47,0:27:00.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,I need to do something \Nto distract myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:41.82,0:28:43.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,The red deer...
Dialogue: 10,0:29:21.28,0:29:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes. You're good!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:23.70,0:29:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They look so alive, you'd probably find the real thing less convincing, Bogud. {/the way you draw it, it's as though they're alive}{book: To protect the purity of departed souls, he\Ncarved red deer on stones for every passing}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:28.95,0:29:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess the spirit of the red deer \Nreally does possess you, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:32.66,0:29:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you try to draw, \Nit turns out spectacular.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:36.00,0:29:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I didn't want to believe\N you'd brought down a red deer,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:40.13,0:29:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which had proved too tough\N even for Koriko.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:43.55,0:29:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why... You lucky rascal!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:45.72,0:29:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:46.68,0:29:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you even managed to make Fayau,\N the fairest woman of our village, your wife!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:50.97,0:29:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You, yes, you, the lucky rascal!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:53.22,0:29:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because word is, you've actually been smitten with Fayau for ages.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:58.69,0:30:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You lecher!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:00.23,0:30:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:01.82,0:30:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really expect us to overlook \Nthat sudden fatherhood? {tlc as well, nc what's hondemotte; in book: In the spring of the following year, Bogud took Fayau as his\Nwife. When he was fifteen, he got his own camp, and by seven¬\Nteen fathered a son.}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:06.46,0:30:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:07.57,0:30:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? The two of you live under\N the same roof, yet you didn't realize it?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:11.95,0:30:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, buddy. Congratulations.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:14.25,0:30:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother is gonna be overjoyed \Nto hold her first grandchild this fall.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:19.08,0:30:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You lucky bastard!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:20.71,0:30:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You, you! Yes, you!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:22.30,0:30:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Fayau?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:23.55,0:30:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:25.67,0:30:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it there, Bogud! \NThere're more plates to paint!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:32.31,0:30:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should've kept that\N to myself this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:36.14,0:30:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I have a loose tongue every now and then.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:39.06,0:30:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:41.06,0:30:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:45.32,0:30:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it! We did it, Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:47.28,0:30:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's the matter, Bogud?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:49.28,0:30:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't keep secrets from me! \NThe elder told me the truth!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:04.38,0:31:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I've poured a part of my soul into this red deer amulet.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:08.30,0:31:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that the deer's spirit will help\N to protect you and our unborn child.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:13.81,0:31:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud...
Dialogue: 10,0:31:15.18,0:31:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:25.02,0:31:27.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,By drawing another person, \Nyou bring misfortune upon him.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:28.36,0:31:31.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,But that curse is powerless \Nagainst the power of the red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:31.95,0:31:35.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,Look, we found our happiness, \Nand we're not about to let go of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:53.14,0:31:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:57.14,0:31:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayon! {no clue, assumed proper name, in book it's the tribe's shaman without any name;}
Dialogue: 10,0:31:58.39,0:31:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:02.52,0:32:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:07.65,0:32:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a picture of a woman.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:09.36,0:32:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's a picture. \NWhat ritual was it carved for? {in book: "This woman. Where does she come from?" he asked the\Nshaman. This was not an image created blindly, but one that\Nsurely had a model. The shaman carefully inspected the features\Nof Fayau's garments and head ornaments.\N"It appears to be a Tangad woman."}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:12.41,0:32:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... The Tangad tribe lives\N along this part of the river.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:16.20,0:32:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder which deity they worship \Nby carving a woman's picture into the stone.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:26.59,0:32:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tangad tribe has a woman \Nthis beautiful among them?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:30.30,0:32:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayon!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:31.42,0:32:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:33.30,0:32:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll attack Tangad!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:35.09,0:32:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? B-But sir, we need to head north \Nas soon as we can.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:39.60,0:32:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, about that...
Dialogue: 10,0:32:41.06,0:32:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The snow on Jinst Uul peak \Ndidn't melt last year. {book: The New Land. It was an ancient legend among Shalab's people:\NWhen the snow on Jinst Uul peak does not melt for an entire\Ncycle ofseasons, in the following year the Northern Corridor leading to the New Land will appear from the depths of the ocean.\NWhen the sun is at its highest, we will cross this corridor to more\Nfertile land, where water and endless pastures abound.}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:43.69,0:32:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we can cross the Northern Corridor this year to the new land
Dialogue: 10,0:32:47.11,0:32:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that we left our homeland for.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:48.61,0:32:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But look at that.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:50.15,0:32:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The long journey's used up nearly \Nall of our food supplies.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:53.61,0:32:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We {\i1}need{\i0} to attack and plunder Tangad for food and warm clothing anyhow.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:57.12,0:33:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they also have a woman this beautiful \Namong them, I'll take her as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:01.12,0:33:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:21.14,0:33:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe my ears, Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:23.89,0:33:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So you {\i1}did{\i0} break that law, after all?!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:26.98,0:33:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You drew a picture of another person?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:31.32,0:33:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. A catastrophe befell\N our whole tribe, not just you.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:36.91,0:33:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Our men slaughtered, our women abducted.\N Food, livestock... They took everything!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:43.16,0:33:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Tangad has been...
Dialogue: 10,0:33:46.04,0:33:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,razed to the ground!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:49.04,0:33:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau... Where's Fayau?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:52.17,0:33:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The northern tribe took her.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:55.72,0:33:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:57.01,0:33:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think you're going?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:58.64,0:34:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:00.56,0:34:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau... I'll save Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:02.81,0:34:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You big dummy! \NYou gonna do that in your current state?!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:08.06,0:34:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's calm down, Bogud.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:12.19,0:34:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been badly injured.\N You slept for three days and three nights.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:16.53,0:34:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Groaning from fever too.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:18.86,0:34:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be sure that the northern tribe is far, far away by now,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:22.54,0:34:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,heading for the Northern Corridor.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:24.37,0:34:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The Northern Corridor?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:25.71,0:34:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a legend of their tribe.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:29.33,0:34:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If the snow doesn't melt \Non Jinst Uul all year round,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:32.88,0:34:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the following year, the Northern Corridor will emerge from the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:37.84,0:34:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,By crossing that, \Nthey're hoping to find the new world.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:41.72,0:34:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The new world?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:43.68,0:34:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind. Similar legends have been passed down in every tribe.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:48.52,0:34:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, some legends say \Nyou need to head south instead of north.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:53.86,0:34:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,South?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:54.78,0:34:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,"Make your way south, and cross the sea \Non a wooden vehicle they call a boat.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:59.61,0:35:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll reach the new world all the same."
Dialogue: 10,0:35:02.74,0:35:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Our tribe was blessed with verdant lands.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:06.08,0:35:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought of abandoning our homeland
Dialogue: 10,0:35:08.04,0:35:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and taking our families on a meandering journey never crossed our minds.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:11.83,0:35:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But the northern tribes weren't so lucky.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:14.55,0:35:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So I suppose their chieftain Shalab\Nfinally decided to take the plunge.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:20.18,0:35:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:22.26,0:35:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After them. To the Northern Corridor.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:25.35,0:35:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to catch up with them \Nas soon as I can and take Fayau back.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:28.77,0:35:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid! It's way too late \Nto catch up with them now.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:32.27,0:35:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud! You're supposed \Nto help me bury the fallen!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:36.57,0:35:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand, Bogud? \N{\i1}You{\i0} brought this disaster upon us!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:10.10,0:36:12.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,The northern tribe probably stops to rest at night.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:12.69,0:36:16.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I ride day and night at full speed, \NI'll catch up with them sooner or later!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:42.07,0:37:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:45.91,0:37:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:54.66,0:37:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau! Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:58.33,0:37:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:00.13,0:38:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:02.17,0:38:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Bogud! Bogud!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:05.76,0:38:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:46.42,0:38:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:48.51,0:38:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau...
Dialogue: 10,0:38:50.72,0:38:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the red deer\N is watching over us!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:54.72,0:38:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...watching over us...
Dialogue: 10,0:38:57.73,0:39:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the red deer will never give up!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:01.73,0:39:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...never give up...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:04.73,0:39:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:07.24,0:39:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:10.74,0:39:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come for you! Believe me!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:43.36,0:39:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert, this is it. Yes, I'm positive.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:46.78,0:39:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This piece is going to be more captivating \Nthan anything I've released so far.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:50.65,0:39:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a relief.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:51.99,0:39:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was well worth the effort \Nof showing you this place.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:54.49,0:39:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's return to the hotel.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:56.41,0:39:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to write down the score tonight.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:58.45,0:40:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd do me a big favor.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:00.50,0:40:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we get back to New York, I'll have\N to make the rounds of studios and players. {/Once we get back to New York, I'll put the studios and performers to work right away.}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:04.50,0:40:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, one more thing, Leslie...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:07.67,0:40:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:40:08.46,0:40:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think I owe you an apology.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:11.30,0:40:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have said it.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:12.72,0:40:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,About the reporter girl and all...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:14.47,0:40:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever. I've forgotten it already.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:24.31,0:40:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:25.69,0:40:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an earthquake!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:42.12,0:40:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How is everyone?! Anyone hurt?!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:44.46,0:40:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, that was one helluva earthquake.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:49.30,0:40:52.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not over. \NThe earthquake will strike again soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:58.22,0:41:01.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,All my life, I've had this mysterious precognition ability.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:18.58,0:41:21.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,I remember what happened \Nmany years ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:21.20,0:41:24.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Back when I lived in San Diego... my grandpa...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:26.13,0:41:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it happened, Flora. \NIn bygone times, our ancestors
Dialogue: 10,0:41:30.71,0:41:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,built a big, big raft and crossed this wide ocean on it.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:35.88,0:41:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay! Big raft! Big raft!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:53.11,0:41:55.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,Jeez, the birthmark's gotten bigger again. {book: When\Nshe removed her hand, she noticed the bluish-purple birthmark\Njust below her left shoulder reflected in the cloudy mirror. The\Nmark had been with her for as long as she could remember, and\N it grew bigger with every passing year. }
Dialogue: 10,0:41:56.70,0:41:59.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,Really, lotsa weird stuff's happening today.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:01.24,0:42:02.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:37.28,0:42:41.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Something unheard of \Nis coming to our island.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:30.96,0:43:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a perfectly and unquestionably \Nisolated island.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:34.46,0:43:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tyler, how far do you think we've drifted?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:40.47,0:43:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I've also been thinking about that \Nfor these past few days.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:44.51,0:43:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we drifted south from the equator, \Nwe're probably somewhere north of Tahiti. {book: In that hectic era, a\Nsolitary boat was drifting in the South Pacific towards Talofa, a\Nsmall island with a twenty-four kilometer radius that still had a\NStone Age culture. }
Dialogue: 10,0:43:48.39,0:43:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Tahiti?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:49.64,0:43:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Tahiti is regularly visited by English ships.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:52.15,0:43:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe one of those could rescue us.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:54.65,0:43:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what I thought, Channing.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:57.19,0:44:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only saying that nonsense \Nbecause it gives you peace of mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:00.40,0:44:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:01.32,0:44:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jones?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:02.66,0:44:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it as well as I do, Tyler.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:04.91,0:44:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If sailing vessels ever visited this place, \Nthe island natives would know about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:09.96,0:44:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't believe me,\N just ask them yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:12.54,0:44:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:13.54,0:44:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody believes it when I tell them \Nabout ships propelled by the wind.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:17.13,0:44:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tell them about giant vessels, holding hundreds of people,
Dialogue: 10,0:44:20.17,0:44:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they just laugh in my face.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:22.09,0:44:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough, Jones.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:23.43,0:44:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They've never seen \Na seafaring ship in their lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:25.85,0:44:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This island is far from any English maritime trade route.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:29.35,0:44:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We're nowhere near Tahiti.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:32.35,0:44:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones, you've said enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:37.02,0:44:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Channing. Hey, Ed Channing!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:47.37,0:44:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You've upset Channing.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:49.29,0:44:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the one on lookout that night.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:52.04,0:44:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter who's on lookout, you can't avoid an underwater volcanic eruption.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:56.75,0:44:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened too suddenly.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:58.55,0:45:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Jones, you should stop \Nblaming that on Channing.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:02.01,0:45:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He's easily disheartened.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:03.88,0:45:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't putting the blame \Non Ed Channing.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:06.93,0:45:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had to blame someone,\NI'd blame you first, Tyler.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:10.68,0:45:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd blame myself for the sins \NI indulged in during those 20 days adrift! {book: Meanwhile, one of the three men, Jones, was dreaming of a\Nbeautiful goddess dancing in the sky, watching over his fallen\Nbody bobbing among the waves. She placed her hand on his chest\Nwith a soft touch that comforted him beyond imagination. Her\Nskin was not white, but her features resembled those of a white\Nperson. Her black hair extended infinitely behind her and Jones\Ncould no longer tell if he was dreaming or not. She leaned forward\Nwith concern in her eyes. He'd always imagined goddesses as ra¬\Ndiant beings clad in white flowing robes, but she had nothing on.\NHer shapely brown breasts swayed above him in full view, and\Njust the sight of them made Jones feel wonderful. Over the past\Ntwenty days adrift at sea, he'd dreamt of many things. In a reality\Nno different than Hell itself, dozing off for even an hour was a\Nwelcome escape. Behind closed eyes, he ate and drank to his\Nheart's content in the cool shade, surrounded by people he loved.\NA number of women appeared in these fantasies, but none so\Nbeautiful as the one before him now. Despite being a man of faith,\Nfor Jones this was the closest he'd ever come to experiencing\NGod's presence in his dreams.}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:15.94,0:45:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over now. \NForget about it and move on!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:18.40,0:45:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't possibly forget it! Twelve sailors took refuge on the boat.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:22.19,0:45:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But only the three of us survived!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:25.41,0:45:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet you were among those three.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:38.96,0:45:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Channing! You clumsy twerp!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:41.21,0:45:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship ran aground \Nbecause you didn't pay attention!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:45.01,0:45:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain! But you were also \Ndead drunk and asleep!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:49.47,0:45:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence! How am I to explain \Nthis enormous loss?!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:52.64,0:45:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship's hold is still\N chock-full of barrels!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:55.39,0:45:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And those barrels are full of whale oil! {for reference, it's whale oil, so maybe replace with "fat" for clarification}
Dialogue: 10,0:45:58.11,0:46:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That oil would fetch a fortune in gold! {lit: oil is traded for gold}
Dialogue: 10,0:46:00.98,0:46:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Save your breath, Captain. \NThere's still a chance the ship won't sink!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:05.24,0:46:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, we should take shelter in the sea, \Nor else we'll get caught in the next eruption!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:10.41,0:46:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be kidding me!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:11.74,0:46:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Another one will blow the ship to smithereens,\N along with our whale oil! {omitted "of those giant explosions " for CPS}
Dialogue: 10,0:46:15.41,0:46:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whale oil is all you care about! \NIf it's so important to you,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:18.96,0:46:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't you return to the ship \Non your own, Captain?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:21.92,0:46:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! I'll do just that, you coward!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:25.05,0:46:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn the boat back, deckhands!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:34.32,0:46:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hopeless!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:59.00,0:47:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Look!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:01.34,0:47:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Look at this!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:04.71,0:47:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Channing?
Dialogue: 10,0:47:06.26,0:47:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The officers' boat is gone.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:08.59,0:47:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No sign of our whaling ship either!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:10.59,0:47:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What? The boats were supposed to be tied together with ropes.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:14.47,0:47:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Also to the raft with all our supplies and water!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:20.40,0:47:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been cut!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:24.57,0:47:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut with a knife.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:27.03,0:47:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?!\NWhat happened last night?!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:30.28,0:47:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How come we can't even see \Nour whaling ship now?!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:36.20,0:47:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The officers abandoned us. \NThat's the only explanation!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:41.12,0:47:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones, do we have any water \Nor provisions on this boat?
Dialogue: 10,0:47:45.13,0:47:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,None, except for a single barrel of wine.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:48.13,0:47:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wine will do for now. All right...
Dialogue: 10,0:47:54.97,0:48:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me, everyone. There's no way\N to know how many days we'll be adrift.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:00.10,0:48:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if we'll be saved at all. \NThat's entirely up to God's grace now.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:04.15,0:48:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll do whatever we can, regardless.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:06.32,0:48:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, I'll be deciding how much wine\N each man gets daily to quench his thirst.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:11.28,0:48:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And I won't tolerate anyone disobeying that rule.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:13.87,0:48:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When you can't take it anymore,\N start cursing the bastards who marooned us!
Dialogue: 10,0:48:30.30,0:48:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first ten days, \Neveryone put up with it.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:34.34,0:48:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But all hell broke loose \Nin the next ten days.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:37.93,0:48:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was at their limit.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:40.27,0:48:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Men started going crazy with thirst, \Nand things were about to turn ugly. {/became extremely violent}
Dialogue: 10,0:48:47.27,0:48:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But Tyler, nobody on that boat \Nwas as fiendish as you.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:51.32,0:48:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You showed no mercy to those\N who transgressed the rules.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:54.32,0:48:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You made Ed Channing and me\Njettison bodies into the sea every day.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:58.49,0:49:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What could I do?
Dialogue: 10,0:49:00.75,0:49:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all in hope of a better tomorrow. {lit: due to hopes directed into tomorrow}
Dialogue: 10,0:49:03.42,0:49:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope? What kind of tomorrow \Ndo you envision for us now?
Dialogue: 10,0:49:08.04,0:49:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That swine...
Dialogue: 10,0:49:10.51,0:49:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take Captain Violet's head \Nfor what he's done.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:13.55,0:49:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... {\i1}my{\i0} hope.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:31.99,0:49:39.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,No... They hadn't caused \Nthat extraordinary sensation.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:56.59,0:49:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Now you've done it!
Dialogue: 10,0:49:58.60,0:49:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 10,0:50:01.60,0:50:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What is he thinking?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:04.10,0:50:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you've been busy, Jones. {lit: you're brazen/gutsy}
Dialogue: 10,0:50:05.94,0:50:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,While resenting our situation, you're actually enjoying your island life, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:10.77,0:50:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that girl's name was Laia?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:13.03,0:50:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a good eye, friend.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:15.11,0:50:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A castaway romance?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:16.91,0:50:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for you, but don't get used to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:19.37,0:50:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:20.53,0:50:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, we'll get out of here \Nand return to England.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:23.20,0:50:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you gonna do with Laia then?\NLeave her behind?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:26.12,0:50:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take her with me, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:28.33,0:50:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Laia agree?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:30.46,0:50:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take her to a bustling city,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:32.50,0:50:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,her island beauty will soon wither. \NDon't you think so?{(as in "she will suffer out of her element")}
Dialogue: 10,0:50:35.92,0:50:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you still love her \Nlike you do now?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:38.97,0:50:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not reproaching you,\N just telling you not to take it to heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:44.39,0:50:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you say so, Tyler, \Nit's been half a year now.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:48.44,0:50:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We've burned countless smoke signals, \Nbut not a single ship has ever stopped by.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:52.98,0:50:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing but seagulls \Ncrapping on it every now and then...
Dialogue: 10,0:50:56.40,0:51:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really starting to lose hope.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:00.24,0:51:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe finding a new wife and settling here isn't such a bad idea, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:03.99,0:51:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Some amenities are missing, but other\N than that, it's a relaxed, carefree paradise.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:21.89,0:51:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a paradise, maybe not.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:23.97,0:51:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But the truth is, \Nthis island bores me to death!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:26.73,0:51:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Channing, let's build a ship.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:28.60,0:51:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A ship?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:29.35,0:51:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I've changed my mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:31.40,0:51:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If no ships are coming our way, \Nwe should build one ourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:34.32,0:51:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a shipwright, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:35.98,0:51:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If the three of us join forces,
Dialogue: 10,0:51:37.69,0:51:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we can build a vessel big enough \Nto take us to another island. Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:42.45,0:51:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:44.87,0:51:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Making a confession.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:47.62,0:51:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Confession? What's a confession?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:49.58,0:51:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I confess my sins to God \Nand ask for forgiveness.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:53.67,0:51:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But God is not here.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:55.55,0:51:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not someone who is {\i1}here{\i0} or {\i1}there{\i0}...
Dialogue: 10,0:51:58.84,0:52:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,God lives on the mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:02.30,0:52:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Laia.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:03.43,0:52:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Laia.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:05.06,0:52:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're going to England with me someday, I need you to remember this.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:10.06,0:52:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,God... is unseen by the eye \Nand imperceptible to touch.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:14.40,0:52:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Laia knows. Laia saw God.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:43.18,0:52:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:44.55,0:52:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. God. Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:49.35,0:52:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez. Where's that loafer Jones \Nwhen you need him?
Dialogue: 10,0:52:52.56,0:52:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told him over and over to help us!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:54.31,0:52:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he probably found some secluded spot \Nand is having a good time with Laia there.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:58.40,0:53:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause she's the only thing on his mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:00.32,0:53:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be kidding me!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:01.90,0:53:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We three need to work on this together, \Nor else we'll never leave this island!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:06.07,0:53:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we could ask the locals for help.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:11.04,0:53:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't getting anything from them, I reckon.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:03.55,0:54:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:07.18,0:54:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:10.72,0:54:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau! Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:18.06,0:54:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Laia?
Dialogue: 10,0:54:19.98,0:54:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau! Fayau!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:29.78,0:54:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing it. I'm crossing the southern seas \Nto the new world.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:33.75,0:54:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Fayau, I'll find you,\N and I'll see you again!
Dialogue: 10,0:55:10.45,0:55:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:14.70,0:55:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We... help you.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:18.04,0:55:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The men of the island\N will help with your work.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:22.54,0:55:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'd... appreciate that.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:25.05,0:55:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have a condition.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:27.47,0:55:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What condition?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:28.59,0:55:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We build a big boat.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:30.89,0:55:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One that takes every person on the island.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:35.39,0:55:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This condition... You accept?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:38.35,0:55:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:40.14,0:55:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Where will the islanders go \Nafter leaving such a nice island?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:43.57,0:55:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to the eastern continent.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:46.53,0:55:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eastern? Maybe he's talking about South America?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:50.07,0:55:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Long ago, our distant ancestor \Ngot stranded on this island.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:54.74,0:56:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened while he was trying to cross\N the sea and get to the eastern continent.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:00.46,0:56:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But he couldn't build a ship big enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:04.04,0:56:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ancestor passed away on this island.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:08.51,0:56:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It is essential that we go east.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:11.72,0:56:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite the news! \NWhy are you only telling me now?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:16.35,0:56:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We forgot. We angered our ancestor.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:20.48,0:56:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:24.52,0:56:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We've woken up to our fate...\Nto leave this island.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:39.29,0:56:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You can't see it?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:42.33,0:56:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot! Did you fall asleep there or what?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:45.75,0:56:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Victor?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:47.80,0:56:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our idiotic lookout let the {\i1}Florence{\i0}\N slip out of sight. {book: . One year and some months later, an\NAmerican privateer dubbed the Rattlesnake dropped anchor in\NTahiti. The Rattlesnake was a pirate ship involved mainly in contraband trade. Since leaving its home port of New Bedford, the\NRattlesnake had been in continuous pursuit of another privateer\Ncalled the Florence, known to be harvesting a spice newly discovered in the South Pacific islands.}
Dialogue: 10,0:56:52.72,0:56:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Frodo, you scallywag! \NYou're not eating tonight! {unsure about name, couldn't find it in book}
Dialogue: 10,0:56:57.10,0:56:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure they didn't notice us?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:59.72,0:57:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not funny, after we've trailed them for so long!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:02.31,0:57:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Those spices are currently \Nthe priciest commodity in the world.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:05.19,0:57:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But the {\i1}Florence{\i0} is hiding\N where they're getting it really well!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:08.19,0:57:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So you decided to follow them in secret \Nto get a piece of it for yourself, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:57:12.49,0:57:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you a cunning devil?
Dialogue: 10,0:57:14.41,0:57:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that they've slipped away, it's a fiasco!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:16.49,0:57:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Blast. All that money, wasted!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:19.12,0:57:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather have your problems after losing\N both my ship and my oil to the sea. {lit: from my point of view, whose ship and whale oil sunk, this is enviable piece of trash}
Dialogue: 10,0:57:23.79,0:57:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I ended up washing up at Tahiti \Nand rotting there for a year.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:28.46,0:57:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Show some gratitude. I only saved you \Nbecause I owe you one! {book: After trailing the Florence for a year, the Rattlesnake fol¬\Nlowed her into Tahiti's harbor. It was there that Victor happened\Nto run into Violet. When they were younger, they'd sailed to¬\Ngether on a three-year voyage, during which Violet had actually\Nsaved Victor's life. So, after meeting again in such an unlikely\Nplace, Victor accepted Violet and his men without question and\Nthey were welcomed aboard the Rattlesnake as members of the\Ncrew. With this, the ship's crew surpassed fifty. The ranks of ruf¬\Nfians from pirate and slave ships reinforced thus, they wouldn't\Nbe outnumbered. Once they found out where the spices grew, Vic¬\Ntor would be more than ready to wage battle with the Florence.}
Dialogue: 10,0:57:57.41,0:58:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not making as much progress \Nas I thought we would.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:00.58,0:58:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Jones.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:02.62,0:58:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard must be out of his mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:05.54,0:58:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he {\i1}ever{\i0} come here\N to lend us a hand?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:08.84,0:58:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All he and Laia ever do is\N go hiking in the mountains!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:11.80,0:58:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're visiting the stone monument \Nwith the engraved red deer.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:16.13,0:58:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When I asked him why, \Nhe said they're looking after it.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:19.89,0:58:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, they mow the grass there, \Npolish the thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:22.31,0:58:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I told him, "Forget about the damn monument and come help us on the beach!"
Dialogue: 10,0:58:25.94,0:58:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That nearly brought him\N to tears, apparently.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:28.52,0:58:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have to listen to my wife now!"
Dialogue: 10,0:58:31.52,0:58:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Tyler, what I've been thinking is...
Dialogue: 10,0:58:33.86,0:58:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder suddenly expressed a wish to head east.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:36.95,0:58:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it also be connected \Nto the restoration of that monument?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:40.74,0:58:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out. You're freaking me out.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:43.41,0:58:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that monument was a vessel\N for their ancestor's despair,
Dialogue: 10,0:58:46.33,0:58:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and now that's transferred\N to the islanders?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:48.88,0:58:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it only affects Laia.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:54.51,0:58:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,See how good I am? Your tattoo is identical to the carving!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:58.13,0:58:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you, Jones.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:00.89,0:59:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Laia, what's this all about?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:03.47,0:59:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we have to tattoo a red deer \Non our shoulders?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:07.06,0:59:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The red deer is our guardian. \NFor Laia and Jones.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:10.19,0:59:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It will protect us and our child.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:12.82,0:59:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our child?{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:59:15.82,0:59:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,L-Laia!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:17.24,0:59:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the red deer protects\N the future of children.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:20.49,0:59:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I really had no idea, Laia.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:22.91,0:59:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great! \NSo we're going to have a baby?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:36.46,0:59:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's useless. They shook us off.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:39.68,0:59:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be helped. \NWe'll track them from Tahiti once more.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:43.22,0:59:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Victor, look at that island.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:44.89,0:59:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:53.52,0:59:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,First time I'm seeing it, \Nbut that's very timely.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:56.44,0:59:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Our freshwater supplies are running low.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:59.24,1:00:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Helmsman, hard to port!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:10.92,1:00:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think it turned out\N not half bad. Right?
Dialogue: 10,1:00:14.79,1:00:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyler, this jerrybuilt thing \Nisn't going anywhere.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:17.96,1:00:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a navigator yourself, so you ought to know.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:21.26,1:00:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying, all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 10,1:00:23.59,1:00:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The islanders are totally invested now!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:29.06,1:00:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just them.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:30.89,1:00:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not boarding this junk.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:33.69,1:00:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a large frame, \Nbut nothing holds it together. {lit is just "it's largely useless"}
Dialogue: 10,1:00:36.44,1:00:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You go tell that to them!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:39.07,1:00:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll watch you getting stoned! {/They'll beat you up without a second thought!}
Dialogue: 10,1:00:41.82,1:00:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Laia?
Dialogue: 10,1:00:43.78,1:00:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:45.56,1:00:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,1:00:46.53,1:00:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What's here?
Dialogue: 10,1:01:06.55,1:01:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Laia!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:36.98,1:01:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 10,1:01:40.17,1:01:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Oh!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:48.80,1:01:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tyler! It's a ship!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:51.18,1:01:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What did you say?
Dialogue: 10,1:01:53.35,1:01:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyler, can you believe they've arrived \Nat such a good time?
Dialogue: 10,1:01:57.06,1:02:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We can go home! We can go back to England on a normal, seaworthy ship!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:01.11,1:02:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Channing!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:02.44,1:02:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:04.24,1:02:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The slipshod raft we put together \Nis nowhere near as safe as that ship!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:08.16,1:02:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our best hope! \NLet's meet the captain and ask for help!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:10.87,1:02:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be so impatient! \NLet's observe the situation first.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:16.12,1:02:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing but a line of clueless faces.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:19.00,1:02:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd probably be happy to fetch all the water we need for a glass ball.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:24.05,1:02:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to disembark!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:25.88,1:02:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Victor.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:27.64,1:02:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That island has more to offer \Nthan just some water.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:31.01,1:02:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:32.60,1:02:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There, hiding in the shadow of that palm tree, \Nan excited crowd of young women.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:37.77,1:02:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single one is an exquisite beauty.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:40.61,1:02:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you getting at?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:42.48,1:02:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Victor! Capturing them and reselling them to a slave trader, of course.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:48.03,1:02:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And who's the cunning devil now?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:50.53,1:02:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready your muskets, you scallywags!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:54.75,1:02:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a ship!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:56.16,1:02:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A normal ship!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:01.59,1:03:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones?
Dialogue: 10,1:03:15.22,1:03:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you get it now? They're pirates!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:17.73,1:03:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh, I don't care if they're pirates.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:19.77,1:03:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If they can save us, \NI don't care what they do for a living!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:22.69,1:03:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it together, Channing.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:25.03,1:03:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We owe the islanders big time\N for what they've done for us.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:28.28,1:03:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take a closer look\N at the pirate captain.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:35.75,1:03:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to rush.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:37.54,1:03:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still stunned by that last volley. {lit: to be unable to stand up due to fear or surprise - meaning they won't charge us so we can take our time reloading the guns}
Dialogue: 10,1:03:40.21,1:03:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Load your muskets slowly.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:43.75,1:03:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:47.05,1:03:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, this is flabbergasting. \NWhy is Violet here?
Dialogue: 10,1:03:50.34,1:03:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No, whatever. That doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:52.43,1:03:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be God's gift to me.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:54.85,1:03:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,O Lord, I am grateful.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:57.14,1:03:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:58.85,1:04:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill him now!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:00.69,1:04:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyler!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:02.69,1:04:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Channing!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:04.27,1:04:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jones, stop Tyler!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:06.48,1:04:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to attack the pirates\N all on his own!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:11.03,1:04:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll just get yourself killed!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:19.79,1:04:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones, by God's grace,\N my boredom is over.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:23.25,1:04:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I can now kill that swine Violet \Nwithout going anywhere.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:26.13,1:04:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But why...
Dialogue: 10,1:04:27.76,1:04:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyler, is it really worth throwing your life away for this?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:31.59,1:04:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten already?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:34.01,1:04:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Before getting here, we had to throw nine of our crewmates into the sea.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:38.35,1:04:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose fault was it?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:41.06,1:04:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet's!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:42.69,1:04:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones, it falls to you to take the islanders\N to the eastern continent.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:47.07,1:04:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Laia fell in love with you.\N It's your fate.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:52.74,1:04:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Channing, have some confidence.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:55.45,1:04:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This vessel you built is magnificent.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:57.49,1:05:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it'll cross the Pacific and beyond in a breeze. Okay, Channing?
Dialogue: 10,1:05:02.16,1:05:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:03.08,1:05:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyler!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:08.92,1:05:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it about time\N we rounded up the women?
Dialogue: 10,1:05:19.22,1:05:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:20.18,1:05:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:23.69,1:05:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How come...
Dialogue: 10,1:05:27.23,1:05:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's him!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:30.86,1:05:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How come...
Dialogue: 10,1:05:34.86,1:05:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he's here?!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:47.67,1:05:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jones!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:49.09,1:05:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Laia, hurry up!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:53.13,1:05:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:54.09,1:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Laia?
Dialogue: 10,1:05:55.68,1:05:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest one yet... is here!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:06.83,1:07:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I-It's a miracle! \NOur raft is afloat!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:18.68,1:07:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Head east, my descendants!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:21.80,1:07:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Cross over to the eastern lands, \Nfollowing the guidance of the red deer.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:48.87,1:07:52.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,Oh jeez. The birthmark darkens more and more.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:57.38,1:08:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how long we've been here.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:00.26,1:08:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost all sense of time a while ago.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:08.27,1:08:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert, what was that?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:10.85,1:08:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, probably deep cave creatures.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:14.48,1:08:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Deep cave creatures?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:16.90,1:08:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Life forms that adapted to living in constant darkness in the depths of the earth.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:21.78,1:08:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But because it's so dark in here, \Nthere's no way to tell what they look like.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:25.91,1:08:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the sound is the only evidence \Nof their existence?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:34.21,1:08:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Leslie? What's so funny?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:36.71,1:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought to myself,
Dialogue: 10,1:08:37.76,1:08:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if Leslie Mardoff disappeared\N without a trace,
Dialogue: 10,1:08:40.55,1:08:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what evidence would be left\N of his existence in our era at all?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:44.76,1:08:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason,\N that seemed funny to me.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:46.93,1:08:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You've released countless pieces already,\N enough to leave a mark.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:51.94,1:08:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe, but it would probably\Nbe my reputation
Dialogue: 10,1:08:55.23,1:08:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as an infamous womanizer,\N involved in many scandals.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:58.28,1:09:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they're all fictions that the media made up on the go.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:02.95,1:09:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The scandals are untrue?
Dialogue: 10,1:09:04.24,1:09:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was too much of a bother, \Nso I never took the trouble to deny them.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:09.91,1:09:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert, I believe firmly there's a person in this world who's destined to be with me.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:15.33,1:09:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Laugh at me for being old-fashioned, \Nbut I've always believed that.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:53.54,1:09:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:55.58,1:09:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Leslie, forgive me.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:57.50,1:10:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have brought you \Nto this god-forsaken place.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:01.05,1:10:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong! We'll be saved!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:04.34,1:10:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone will save us.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:05.63,1:10:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I don't know why, \Nbut that's what my intuition says.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:08.80,1:10:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because you're still young. {he says that because he's old, bitter, and disillusioned}
Dialogue: 10,1:10:11.81,1:10:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's because I believe in destiny!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:36.75,1:10:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert... Gilbert!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:54.06,1:10:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:02.40,1:11:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a tsunami!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:03.78,1:11:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That last earthquake caused a tsunami \Nin the underground lake!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:07.61,1:11:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilbert!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:09.87,1:11:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Is someone there?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:13.08,1:11:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! We're here!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:15.66,1:11:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on! I'll lower the rope now!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:26.92,1:11:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:31.51,1:11:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be the deep cave creatures.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:33.85,1:11:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The light emitted by creatures living\N in constant darkness proves they really exist!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:39.02,1:11:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Catch the rope!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:59.16,1:12:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Can't you lower\N the rope a little more?
Dialogue: 10,1:12:07.49,1:12:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 10,1:12:08.67,1:12:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The rope! Just a little lower!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.42,1:13:38.85,Songs,,0,0,0,,When you fall in love with someone {誰かを好きになる時は}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.27,1:13:46.44,Songs,,0,0,0,,The excitement pushes you forward {ときめきが背中を押すのね}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.07,1:13:54.40,Songs,,0,0,0,,With just a glance at your profile {まばたき あなたの横顔} {/face in profile}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.86,1:14:01.91,Songs,,0,0,0,,I fall in love with you before I know it {突然にいとしくなるの}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.91,1:14:09.59,Songs,,0,0,0,,I fell in love long ago {はるか昔恋におちた}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.59,1:14:17.43,Songs,,0,0,0,,But it feels strange, as if we're inside a myth {神話ほどの不思議さ感じる}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.43,1:14:29.19,Songs,,0,0,0,,When I'm with you, my heart fills with light {あなたがいて心すべて\Nきらめくから}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.19,1:14:33.07,Songs,,0,0,0,,Warming me up even during the coldest winter {季節もやさしい}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.07,1:14:40.95,Songs,,0,0,0,,It's dizzying to follow the fate of a shooting star {きっとめまいしながら 流れ星のさだめに}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.95,1:14:48.63,Songs,,0,0,0,,But it'll lead the two of us down the path of love {二人導かれて愛になる}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.30,1:15:07.73,Songs,,0,0,0,,Intuition tells me that our encounter is no coincidence {偶然でもゆきずりでも}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.15,1:15:15.94,Songs,,0,0,0,,And it is surely bound to last {ない出逢いを直感してるの}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.94,1:15:23.74,Songs,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who can reach my heart {あなただけで心染まる}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.74,1:15:31.59,Songs,,0,0,0,,But it's so painful, I can't find the words {苦しいほど言葉も出なくて}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.59,1:15:39.30,Songs,,0,0,0,,Even if it's going to be dizzying, \NI'll follow you to the ends of the earth {だからめまいしながら ついて行くわあなたに}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.30,1:15:47.14,Songs,,0,0,0,,I always knew it would come to this {きっと決っていた こうなると}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.14,1:15:54.94,Songs,,0,0,0,,It'll be dizzying for sure, \Nbut I know I'll fall in love with you {きっとめまいしながら 恋におちる自分を}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.94,1:16:01.82,Songs,,0,0,0,,I know I won't be able to stop loving you {きっと止められない愛してる}
